Here we will instead look at the differences between observed and expected cumulative proportions. Letting Ci and Ei denote the observed and expected case counts in zone i, our observed test statistic is
(18)d+=(1/C)maxk=1,…,K-1{∑i=1kCi-∑i=1kEi}
where K is the number of zones. This is simply the one-sided Kolmogorov–Smirnov statistic. Although tables of critical values are most commonly used to assess significance, these can be unduly conservative when the underlying distribution is discrete, as it is here.12
